parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat heater amp can cause a fire hazard, potentially leading to injuries or damage.
symptoms: The seat heater stops working
and a burnt connector is found.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door locks can cause inconvenience, safety risks, and potential security breaches.
symptoms: The front driver and passenger door locks fail to work intermittently
with no specific pattern or trigger.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights and instrumentation can cause accidents, especially at night, and reduce driver visibility.
symptoms: The headlights
taillights
and dashboard lights turn off intermittently when using the turn signal
typically at night and in cold temperatures.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trailer brake controller can cause accidents, especially when towing heavy loads, and lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The trailer brake controller fails to apply brakes or provide adequate braking power
even when set to the highest setting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the low note electric horn can cause accidents, especially in cold temperatures, and reduce driver safety.
symptoms: The low note electric horn becomes inoperative below 25 degrees Fahrenheit.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of daytime instrument panel illumination can cause driver distraction, accidents, and reduce safety.
symptoms: The dashboard instruments are barely discernible during the day
even with sunglasses.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rodent damage to wiring can cause electrical failures, accidents, and reduce safety.
symptoms: Rodents damage wiring
resulting in costly repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the integrated brake controller can lead to inadequate braking of the trailer, causing accidents or loss of control, especially when towing heavy loads.
symptoms: The brake controller fails to apply sufficient power to the trailer brakes
the trailer brakes do not lock up when the truck brakes are applied
the manual slider must be used to engage the trailer brakes
and the brake controller settings do not provide adequate braking even at the highest gain setting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear bumper bracket can cause the bumper to detach, leading to accidents, injuries, and road hazards.
symptoms: The bumper detaches or cracks when stepped on
the bumper reinforcement bracket fractures
the bumper cover is damaged
and the vehicle's alarm system is affected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for recall repair can lead to delays in fixing the safety issue, putting drivers and passengers at risk.
symptoms: Dealerships do not have the necessary parts to complete the recall repair
and the manufacturer is unable to provide a timeline for when the parts will be available.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rust on the rear seat frame can lead to structural damage and compromise the vehicle's safety.
symptoms: Rust is visible on the frame of the rear seat
and the dealer attributes the cause to moisture entering the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deployment of air bags can cause injuries and accidents, especially if it occurs unexpectedly.
symptoms: The driver's and passenger's side curtain air bags deploy during a thunderstorm
causing the vehicle to run off the road.
